title: Horrible Customer Service
text: I’ve used Airbnb for years and never experienced and issue, until I did encounter one, and my lord it’s the worst and most powerless customer service department I’ve dealt with. They will close out open cases without fulling their duties. They point to their policies as a way of preventing any action items. They do not value customer’s safety nor feedback. Read the reviews, all true regarding customer service nightmare.

title: Exemplary customer service
text: From beginning to end, each customer service representative performed at the highest level of assistance that anyone could ever wish for. I was particularly impressed with Rihanna who was patient and very knowledgeable. She was smooth, confident and thorough as she explained the process and expectations.

title: Be very wary
text: This app is blatantly misleading. They hide the real prices from you until you actually hit reserve in an obvious bid to get you to pay more than you intended. They let you filter by price but only price per night and because the fees they add on can be anywhere from 30-150 dollars per night it’s actually useless for getting properties in your price range. If you’re using a price filter doesn’t that probably mean you have a budget for your stay and so you want a filter for the total price? They obviously know that but it’s just a shameless attempt to force you to scroll through overbudget properties to price anchor you higher and tire you out until you give in and pay more than what you intended. Very misleading and manipulative. My guess is that most of their five star ratings are from years ago. I would attach screenshots to illustrate my point but I guess the App Store doesn’t let you do that.

title: Frustrated Super Host
text:
We’re Superhosts and have hosted on Airbnb for many years. Mostly, our experience has been positive…and much better than VRBO which was a terrible app. But there is something they need to fix before it comes up again for me.

First of all, however, I’m not a fan of the options available when setting up our cancellation policy for our guests. For a full refund, you can set it up for 24 hours out, 5 days, or 30 days. No differentiation between 1-night stays, which aren’t a big deal and week+ stays which are.

But my current frustration is that I recently had a one-night guest cancel 4 days in advance due to a family emergency. I told them if they cancel, I could refund their money. I’d done this for other guests in the past. But after they canceled, I found out this feature had been changed, and I could no longer do what I’d promised. I had to go through the support team, explaining the situation, having the representative misunderstand, explaining it again, and having them do what I should’ve been able to do myself. And oh the joys of a representative telling you how to navigate the app when you already know how to use it well and know what they’re telling you won’t work.

Fix this please. If a guest cancels, and I wish to refund their money, I want the ability to take care of it myself.
